TO BUILD:

In the root directory:

> make

TO RUN SERVER

It is important to launch bankserver from ./bin so that it finds the accounts file.
It is not necessary to give the server a port number. The OS chooses one.

> cd ./bin
> ./bankserver (exits after RPC registration; service continues to run)

TO RUN CLIENT

> ./bankclient input_file

OR

> ./bankclient [command]

OUTPUT:

Accounts balance is written to the text file /bin/accounts .
Messages for user are printed to stdout/stderr .

TO GET HELP:

> ./bankclient 
> ./bankclient -h
> ./bankclient --help